# Repo Map — agent-skills

## Purpose
Central registry for versioned Agent Skills. Skills are authored here,
then deployed to `~/.cursor/skills/`, `~/.agents/skills/`, or
`~/.claude/skills/` via `scripts/skill-sync.sh`.

## Key paths

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `skills/<name>/` | Skill source — SKILL.md + metadata.json + optional refs/assets/scripts |
| `skill-registry.json` | Central manifest — version, author, scope, targets per skill |
| `scripts/skill-sync.sh` | Deploy skills to target paths |
| `scripts/skill-version.sh` | Bump version across registry + metadata + SKILL.md |
| `scripts/skill-import.sh` | Import a skill from an external project |
| `packages/react-best-practices-build/` | Build tooling for rules-based skills (AGENTS.md compilation) |
| `.cursor/skills/skill-registry/` | Meta-skill for registry management |

## Skill directory structure

Every skill MUST have `SKILL.md` and `metadata.json` at minimum.

```
skills/<name>/
├── SKILL.md          # Required — agent instructions
├── metadata.json     # Required — version, author, date, abstract
├── README.md         # Optional — human-facing docs (excluded from deploy)
├── AGENTS.md         # Optional — compiled output (for rules-based skills)
├── references/       # Optional — on-demand docs
├── assets/           # Optional — templates, checklists, quickref
├── scripts/          # Optional — executable automation
└── rules/            # Optional — individual rule files (compiled into AGENTS.md)
```

## Two skill archetypes

1. **Rules-based** (react-best-practices, composition-patterns, react-native-skills):
   Have `rules/` dir compiled into `AGENTS.md` by the build system.
   Editing: add/modify files in `rules/`, then run the build.

2. **Standard** (all others): Direct SKILL.md + references.
   Editing: modify files directly.

## Registry invariant
`skill-registry.json` must always reflect the current state.
When adding/removing/versioning a skill, update the registry.
